UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'Many animals communicate with each other using a variety of sounds, scents, and visual signals, for example, birds may use songs, insects may use pheromones, and chimpanzees may use facial expressions.  Which sentence best exemplifies the use of a semicolon in the passage? Researchers note that the pattern described above remained consistent across repeated observations, suggesting the finding was not a one-time anomaly. They caution that local conditions can still vary, yet the overall relationship held in each documented case.',
  question_text = 'Which sentence in this passage correctly uses a semicolon to separate two independent clauses?',
  stimulus_type = NULL,
  options = '[{"id":"A","text":"Many animals communicate with each other using a variety of sounds, scents, and visual signals; for example, birds may use songs.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"The semicolon is used correctly in choice A to separate two independent clauses. The first clause is \"Many animals communicate with each other using a variety of sounds, scents, and visual signals.\" The second clause is \"for example, birds may use songs.\" Both clauses could stand alone as complete s. Choice A matches the question''s requirement and is consistent with the passage''s central claim or supporting detail. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"B","text":"Many animals communicate with each other using a variety of sounds, scents, and visual signals, for example; birds may use songs.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"This choice does not follow from the information given or contains a calculation error. Choice B is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"C","text":"Many animals communicate with each other using a variety of sounds, scents, and visual signals; birds may use songs, insects may use pheromones, and chimpanzees may use facial expressions.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"This choice does not follow from the information given or contains a calculation error. Choice C is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"D","text":"Many animals communicate with each other using a variety of sounds; scents, and visual signals, for example, birds may use songs.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"