  stimulus_text = 'The use of commas and semicolons is important in writing because they can help to make a text more clear and readable.  There are a number of rules that govern the use of commas and semicolons.   One of the most common errors that writers make is misusing commas and semicolons.  For example, a writer might use a comma to separate two independent clauses when they should use a semicolon. What is the most likely reason why writers misuse commas and semicolons?',
